{#
    Shared Macros for Model README Generation

    Common macros used by both the repository README and Hugging Face model card.
    Includes model intro, license, references, community, and usage sections.
#}


{#
    Generate the model introduction section.

    Parameters
    ----------
    model_name : str
        Display name of the model.
    source_repo : str
        URL to the original repository this model was sourced from.
    model_url : str
        URL to the model page on AI Hub.
    qaihm_model_url : str, optional
        URL to the model's folder in the AI Hub Models GitHub repository.
    is_hf_readme : bool, optional
        Whether generating for Hugging Face (default: False).
#}
{%- macro model_intro(
    model_name,
    source_repo,
    model_url,
    qaihm_model_url=None,
    is_hf_readme=False
) -%}
{% if source_repo -%}
This is based on the implementation of {{ model_name }} found [here]({{ source_repo }}).
{% endif -%}
{%- if is_hf_readme -%}
This repository contains pre-exported model files optimized for Qualcomm® devices. You can use the [Qualcomm® AI Hub Models]({{ qaihm_model_url }}) library to export with custom configurations.
{%- else -%}
This repository contains scripts for optimized on-device export suitable to run on Qualcomm® devices.
{%- endif %} More details on model performance across various devices, can be found [here]({{ '#performance-summary' if is_hf_readme else model_url }}).

Qualcomm AI Hub Models uses [Qualcomm AI Hub Workbench](https://workbench.aihub.qualcomm.com) to compile, profile, and evaluate this model. [Sign up](https://myaccount.qualcomm.com/signup) to run these models on a hosted Qualcomm® device.
{%- endmacro -%}


{#
    Generate a pip install code block.

    Parameters
    ----------
    model_id : str
        Model identifier (e.g., "resnet50").
    has_model_requirements : bool
        Whether model has additional pip requirements.
    pip_pre_build_reqs : str, optional
        Pre-build pip requirements to install first.
    pip_install_flags : str, optional
        Additional flags for pip install command.
    python_version_gte : str, optional
        Minimum Python version (default: "3.10").
    python_version_lt : str, optional
        Maximum Python version (default: "3.14").
#}
{%- macro _pip_install_block(
    model_id,
    has_model_requirements,
    pip_pre_build_reqs=None,
    pip_install_flags=None,
    python_version_gte=None,
    python_version_lt=None
) -%}
{% set install_package = '"qai-hub-models[' ~ (model_id | replace('_', '-')) ~ ']"' if has_model_requirements else 'qai-hub-models' %}
```bash
# NOTE: {{ python_version_gte or '3.10' }} <= PYTHON_VERSION < {{ python_version_lt or '3.14' }} is supported.
{% if pip_pre_build_reqs %}
pip install {{ pip_pre_build_reqs }}
{% endif %}
pip install {{ install_package }}{{ ' ' ~ pip_install_flags if pip_install_flags else '' }}
```
{%- endmacro -%}


{#
    Generate package installation instructions.

    Parameters
    ----------
    model_id : str
        Model identifier (e.g., "resnet50").
    has_model_requirements : bool
        Whether model has additional pip requirements.
    pip_pre_build_reqs : str, optional
        Pre-build pip requirements to install first.
    pip_install_flags : str, optional
        Additional flags for pip install command.
    pip_install_flags_gpu : str, optional
        GPU-specific pip install flags; if provided, shows GPU instructions.
    python_version_gte : str, optional
        Minimum Python version (default: "3.10").
    python_version_lt : str, optional
        Maximum Python version (default: "3.14").
#}
{%- macro package_instructions(
    model_id,
    has_model_requirements,
    pip_pre_build_reqs=None,
    pip_install_flags=None,
    pip_install_flags_gpu=None,
    python_version_gte=None,
    python_version_lt=None
) -%}
Install the package via pip:
{{ _pip_install_block(model_id, has_model_requirements, pip_pre_build_reqs, pip_install_flags, python_version_gte, python_version_lt) }}
{%- if pip_install_flags_gpu %}

For {{ model_id }}, some additional functionality can be faster or is available
only with a GPU on the host machine.

- 🟢 Exporting the model for on-device deployment (GPU not required)
- 🟡 Running the demo (GPU recommended for speed, but not required)
- 🟡 Running evaluation (GPU recommended for speed, but not required)
- 🔴 Quantizing the model (GPU required)

If you are quantizing your own variant of {{ model_id }}, a dedicated CUDA enabled
GPU (40 GB VRAM for 3B models to 80 GB VRAM for 8B models) is recommended. A GPU
can also increase the speed of evaluation and demo of your quantized model
significantly but it not strictly required.

Install the GPU package via pip:
{{ _pip_install_block(model_id, has_model_requirements, pip_pre_build_reqs, pip_install_flags_gpu, python_version_gte, python_version_lt) }}
{%- endif %}
{%- endmacro -%}


{#
    Generate the "Quick Start" section.

    Parameters
    ----------
    model_name : str
        Display name of the model.
    assets_shareable : bool
        Whether pre-exported assets are downloadable via the CLI.
    default_runtime : str
        CLI runtime name for the sample fetch command (e.g., "tflite").
    default_precision : str
        CLI precision name for the sample fetch command (e.g., "float").
#}
{%- macro download_assets(model_name, assets_shareable, default_runtime, default_precision) -%}
## Quick Start

Use our lightweight command-line interface to inspect{{ " and download" if assets_shareable else "" }} {{ model_name }}:

```bash
pip install qai_hub_models_cli # (the CLI is also available with the qai-hub-models package)

{% if assets_shareable %}
# Inspect the model and list the available download options
{% else %}
# Inspect the model's metadata
{% endif %}
qai-hub-models info {{ model_name }}

# Print performance and accuracy metrics
qai-hub-models perf {{ model_name }}
qai-hub-models numerics {{ model_name }}
{% if assets_shareable %}

# Download a ready-to-deploy asset
qai-hub-models fetch {{ model_name }} --runtime {{ default_runtime }} --precision {{ default_precision }}
{% else %}

# Pre-exported assets are not available to download for this model due to
# licensing restrictions. Continue to the next section to export it yourself.
{% endif %}
```
See the [CLI README](../../../../cli/README.md)
for the full list of commands and filters.
{%- endmacro -%}


{#  Generate AI Hub Workbench configuration instructions.  #}
{%- macro configure_aihub() -%}
Sign-in to [Qualcomm® AI Hub Workbench](https://workbench.aihub.qualcomm.com/) with your
Qualcomm® ID. Once signed in navigate to `Account -> Settings -> API Token`.

With this API token, you can configure your client to run models on the cloud
hosted devices.
```bash
qai-hub configure --api_token API_TOKEN
```
Navigate to [docs](https://workbench.aihub.qualcomm.com/docs/) for more information.
{%- endmacro -%}


{#
    Generate the example and usage section with setup, demo, and export instructions.

    Parameters
    ----------
    model_id : str
        Model identifier (e.g., "resnet50").
    model_package : str
        Python package path (e.g., "qai_hub_models.models.resnet50").
    supported_precisions : list[str]
        List of supported precisions (e.g., ["float", "int8"]).
    has_on_target_demo : bool
        Whether the model supports on-device demo.
    has_model_requirements : bool
        Whether model has additional pip requirements.
    pip_pre_build_reqs : str, optional
        Pre-build pip requirements to install first.
    pip_install_flags : str, optional
        Additional flags for pip install command.
    pip_install_flags_gpu : str, optional
        GPU-specific pip install flags.
    python_version_gte : str, optional
        Minimum Python version (default: "3.10").
    python_version_lt : str, optional
        Maximum Python version (default: "3.14").
    readme_install_system_deps : str, optional
        Text describing system-level dependencies to install.
    is_hf_readme : bool, optional
        Whether generating for Hugging Face (default: False).
    readme_export_device : str, optional
        When set, appends ``--device "<value>"`` to the export command. Resolved
        from the global default device when ``requires_aot_prepare`` is set in
        manifest.yaml.
    local_device_deployment : bool, optional
        When set, the Setup / Verify with CLI Demo / Export the model artifact
        sections are nested (one level deeper) under a single "## Export"
        parent. Used by genie LLM models whose local-device deployment section
        links to the "#export" anchor.
    default_runtime : str, optional
        CLI runtime name (e.g., "tflite") rendered into the sample
        ``qai-hub-models export`` command as ``--target-runtime <default_runtime>``.
    default_precision : str, optional
        CLI precision name (e.g., "float") rendered into the sample
        ``qai-hub-models export`` command. For quantize-job models it becomes
        ``--precision``; for separate_quantize_script models it becomes the
        ``--checkpoint DEFAULT_<PRECISION>`` suffix.
    separate_quantize_script : bool, optional
        If True, render a pre-quantized ``--checkpoint DEFAULT_<PRECISION>`` export
        command with an optional quantize-your-own step, instead of the single
        ``--precision`` export command.
#}
{%- macro example_and_usage(
    model_id,
    model_package,
    supported_precisions,
    has_on_target_demo,
    has_model_requirements,
    pip_pre_build_reqs=None,
    pip_install_flags=None,
    pip_install_flags_gpu=None,
    python_version_gte=None,
    python_version_lt=None,
    readme_install_system_deps=None,
    is_hf_readme=False,
    readme_export_device=None,
    local_device_deployment=False,
    default_runtime=None,
    default_precision=None,
    separate_quantize_script=False
) -%}
{%- set precisions_str = "{ --quantize " ~ (supported_precisions | reject('equalto', 'float') | join(', ')) ~ " }" if supported_precisions and supported_precisions|length > 1 and not separate_quantize_script else "" -%}
{%- set step = namespace(num=1) -%}
{# Header levels shift one deeper when nesting under a single "## Export" parent. #}
{%- set h_setup = "###" if local_device_deployment else "##" -%}
{%- set h_step = "####" if local_device_deployment else "###" -%}
{% if local_device_deployment %}
## Export

{{ h_setup }} Setup
{% else %}
{{ h_setup }} Setup
{% endif %}
{% if readme_install_system_deps %}
{{ h_step }} {{ step.num }}. Install System-Level Dependencies
{%- set step.num = step.num + 1 %}

{{ readme_install_system_deps }}
{% endif %}
{{ h_step }} {{ step.num }}. Install the package
{% set step.num = step.num + 1 %}
{{ package_instructions(model_id, has_model_requirements, pip_pre_build_reqs, pip_install_flags, pip_install_flags_gpu, python_version_gte, python_version_lt) }}

{{ h_step }} {{ step.num }}. Configure Qualcomm® AI Hub Workbench
{{ configure_aihub() }}

{{ h_setup }} {{ "Verify with CLI Demo" if local_device_deployment else "Run CLI Demo" }}
Run the following simple CLI demo to verify the model is working end to end:

```bash
python -m {{ model_package }}.demo{{ ' ' ~ precisions_str if precisions_str else '' }}
```
More details on the CLI tool can be found with the `--help` option.{% if not is_hf_readme %} See
[demo.py](demo.py) for sample usage of the model including pre/post processing
scripts. Please refer to our [general instructions on using
models](../../../#getting-started) for more usage instructions.{% endif %}

{% if has_on_target_demo %}

By default, the demo will run locally in PyTorch. Pass `--eval-mode on-device` to the demo script to run the model on a cloud-hosted target device.
{% endif %}

{{ h_setup }} {{ "Export the model artifact" if local_device_deployment else "Export for on-device deployment" }}
To run the model on Qualcomm® devices, you must export the model for use with an edge runtime such as
TensorFlow Lite, ONNX Runtime, or Qualcomm AI Engine Direct.
{% if separate_quantize_script %}
Export the pre-quantized model (published on AI Hub) for on-device deployment:
```bash
qai-hub-models export {{ model_id }} --checkpoint DEFAULT_{{ default_precision | upper }} --target-runtime {{ default_runtime }}{{ ' --device "' ~ readme_export_device ~ '"' if readme_export_device else '' }}
```
`--checkpoint` also accepts `DEFAULT` (the model's default precision){% if supported_precisions and supported_precisions|length > 1 %} or any of
{%- for p in supported_precisions %} `DEFAULT_{{ p | upper }}`{{ ',' if not loop.last }}{% endfor %}{% endif %}.

Optionally, quantize your own variant first and export the resulting checkpoint:
```bash
python -m {{ model_package }}.quantize --precision {{ default_precision }} --output-dir ./quantized_checkpoint
qai-hub-models export {{ model_id }} --checkpoint ./quantized_checkpoint --target-runtime {{ default_runtime }}{{ ' --device "' ~ readme_export_device ~ '"' if readme_export_device else '' }}
```
{% else %}
Use the following command to export the model:
```bash
qai-hub-models export {{ model_id }}{{ ' --target-runtime ' ~ default_runtime if default_runtime else '' }}{{ ' --precision ' ~ default_precision if default_precision else '' }}{{ ' --device "' ~ readme_export_device ~ '"' if readme_export_device else '' }}
```
{% endif %}
Additional options are documented with the `--help` option.
{%- endmacro -%}


